Key Match Events: The Atlanta Braves scored four times in the 10th inning to beat the Minnesota Twins 8-6.
Matt Olson drove in the go-ahead run on a fielder’s choice, Travis d’Arnaud added an RBI single and Ramón Laureano put the game away with a two-run double.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves won the series 3-0 against the Twins.
The attendance at Target Field was 20,200.
The game was played on August 28, 2024, at 11:40 PM in Minneapolis, Minnesota.
